13/06/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- EU External Relations chief Chris Patten said on Friday (11 June) during his visit to Croatia that he is very hopeful the European Council will back the country's EU membership application. He advised the government not to focus on specific dates for negotiations on EU entry but to ensure that the task is completed successfully. He added that he is highly positive about Croatia's prospects. (HINA - 13/06/04)
